phrases: Oh yeah, did you hear about class D?
Crap, I sort of want them too.
Sorry, did I keep you waiting?
There've been lots of rumors about Sadako lately.
Especially since what happened last time.
What is she really like anyway?
I remember seeing her with Kazehaya.
I wonder if they are going out?
I can imagine him liking her.
You know what he is like, he cannot help but be nice.
If anything it would be you.
That is just because we were in the same middle school.
You should just go out with him.
You might not like him, but he might start liking you.
some strange things have been happening around me.
Hey, come on, make a funny face.
I am so surprised and I cannot explain it,
but I am happy that I am not being avoided.
They are saying good things happen when you laugh.
No one's ever said that about me.
Pops yelled at me for drinking pop!
Why do you look like that when you smile?
You are totally friends with Hirano-chan and Endou-chan now, Sadako.
This is the best time of my life.
Hey, can I call you by your first name?
You can call us Chizu or Yano-chin or Ayane or whatever.
Thanks for filling in for me.
That is how you start calling each other by your first names.
Usually it just sort of happens.
We are talking to you too.
That is a lot of Ahs and Chis.
You are stiff enough as it is.
Why do not you start calling the girls by their first name?
You are really awkward, are not you?
I guess it will take a while.
Start with your close friends, maybe.
Here comes a good practice target.
Try calling him by his first name.
You think you can fit in with everyone like that?
Were not you going to try harder?
See, I told you, it is too hard on guys.
That is why I said to start with the girls.
I will talk to the guys like normal for now.
Oh, you made her do it.
He talks nicely to everyone, regardless of gender,
like Yano-san and Yoshida-san do for me.
I was wondering what you were going to say.
He is different from Yano-san and Yoshida-san.
We are choosing the sports day committee today.
The P.E. committee can do it.
He did not even let anyone volunteer.
By the way, I am also the committee representative.
You better show up, or I will tell everyone about your embarrassing
I get it, I will go.
We are kind of short on people, so if you end up competing in more than one sport you need to be athletic.
If you have been in an event before, you need to be in it again.
If you are slow, you better not come.
It is the twice-a-year festival in my name.
I better not drag them down.
You can take the day off.
Why do not we practice during lunch then?
I do not feel like it, but it will probably be fun with Kazehaya.
Kazehaya did not even have a chance to say no before he got chosen.
I wonder if we are going to choose sports day events.
Oh yeah, Kazehaya's going to be the committee member representing class D.
You might even end up going out.
I told you, that would not happen.
I do not mind joining the committee though.
I guess we cannot throw you in at the deep end.
We should start you off with kicking first.
We all sort of expected it.
She should just laugh it off.
She might even scare the opponents that way.
Maybe she will bring us good luck and we will win.
We better head back, we are going to be late for fifth period.
But the clubs use the fields after school.
It is only practice and I am already dragging them down.
I cannot use up their precious time.
It is like he is chilling as usual.
I have never seen him exercising.
I wonder what he looks like playing softball.
We are going to be late for fifth period.
I was not even close to him.
I just could not stop watching him.
I am going to get fat hanging out with you.
Anyway, did not you need to go shopping?
Yeah, I need a red t-shirt, so that I stand out on sports day.
You are coming too, right, Sadako?
I have to water the plants and stuff.
We can go shopping after that.
It will be faster if we help.
Knowing them, they would probably help me with practice too.
I will ask you when you are not busy.
What are you doing later, Kazehaya?
You want to borrow the soccer ball?
It is not for personal use.
I will bring it back, I swear.
I guess I will have to buy my own ball.
I will use my New Year's gift money.
This is where I first talked to Kazehaya-kun.
Huh, you are a committee member too?
Let us make the best of it.
Oh yeah, thanks for the CD.
There is one I want to borrow off of you too.
Sure, I will bring it here.
That album I lent you before the last one
My bad, what were you saying?
That CD before the one I lent you.
Okay, I will bring it next time.
Where the heck are you going?
Something is different about the wind.
